<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE66A59FD1C93E61CD8BC73" pageId="29" pageNumber="787" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE66A59FD1C93E61CD8BC73" blockId="29.[731,1323,1392,1819]" lastBlockId="29.[112,1321,1824,3279]" pageId="29" pageNumber="787">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE66A59FD1C93E61DF8BED2" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[736,1016,1471,1504]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Tylonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="787" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachypus">Tylonycteris pachypus</taxonomicName>
previously included 1 fulvida as a subspecies, but molecular data support the recognition of the latter as a distinct species. Populations outside 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFE66A59FCDC90381D95BD4C" box="[800,917,1633,1662]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="29" pageNumber="787">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and Borneo have not been recently compared to other populations, and more phylogenetic and morphological studies are needed encompassing the full distribution of all species of Tylonyctenis. Three subspecies tentatively recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
